cs.FL, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of a specific type of automata, namely Register Pushdown Automata. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as RPDA is a model of a query language for structured documents with data values. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of problems related to RPDA. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as RPDA can be seen as a logical formalism for handling data values. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of decision problems related to RPDA.
